## Coroutine Handling

### Always Use viewModelScope + Always Rethrow CancellationException
```kotlin
fun loadData() {
    viewModelScope.launch {
        try {
            val data = repository.fetchData()
            _uiState.update { MyFeatureUiState.Data(data) }
        } catch (e: CancellationException) {
            throw e  // Never swallow — coroutine cancellation must propagate
        } catch (e: Exception) {
            _error.emit(e)
        }
    }
}
```

### Dispatcher Rules in ViewModels

`viewModelScope.launch` defaults to `Dispatchers.Main`. Always be explicit about the context for each operation:

```kotlin
fun loadData() {
    viewModelScope.launch {                              // Main (UI coordination)
        _uiState.update { Loading }                     // UI update → Main ✅

        val raw = withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {          // network/DB call → IO ✅
            repository.fetchData()
        }

        val uiItems = withContext(Dispatchers.Default) { // CPU mapping → Default ✅
            raw.map { it.mapToUI() }.toPersistentList()
        }

        _uiState.update { Data(uiItems) }               // UI update → back on Main ✅
    }
}
```

Rules:
- **`Dispatchers.Main`** — only for `_uiState.update {}`, navigation calls, and other UI-facing operations
- **`Dispatchers.IO`** — wrap every suspend call that does network, database, or file I/O with `withContext(Dispatchers.IO) { }`
- **`Dispatchers.Default`** — wrap every CPU-bound transform (sorting, mapping large lists, parsing) with `withContext(Dispatchers.Default) { }`

### Prevent Overlapping Coroutines

For any operation that can be triggered multiple times (search, refresh, start), use a `Job?` to cancel the previous run:

```kotlin
private var loadJob: Job? = null

fun start() {
    loadJob?.cancel()
    loadJob = viewModelScope.launch {
        repository.stream().collect { data ->
            val uiItems = withContext(Dispatchers.Default) { data.map { it.mapToUI() } }
            _uiState.update { Data(uiItems) }
        }
    }
}
```

### Use collectLatest for Flows
```kotlin
viewModelScope.launch {
    repository.items.collectLatest { items ->
        val uiItems = withContext(Dispatchers.Default) { items.map { it.mapToUI() } }
        _uiState.update { MyFeatureUiState.Data(uiItems) }
    }
}
```

